headline: Credit Card Annual Fees Are Going Up. What It Means for the Stocks.
summary: Credit card issuers are trying to attract more higher-end customers with the promise of more rewards.  Chase announced new perks for holders of its Sapphire Reserve credit cards on Tuesday, including a new points boost program, expanded access to airport lounges, and promotional spending credits with partners such as  Apple Lyft DoorDash  StubHub, and Peloton.  The question now, though, is how Chase competitors react to the news of the fee hike.
